Sentencas: Perovskite-based composite cathodes, La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF)-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9-carbonate (SDCC), were investigated as cathode materials for low-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Carbonate-Based Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite (LSCF)-Samarium-Doped Ceria (SDC) Composite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The LSCF was mixed with the SDC-carbonate (SDCC) composite electrolyte at different weight percentages (i.e., 30, 40, and 50 wt %) to prepare the LSCF-SDCC composite cathode.
Titulo: Carbonate-Based Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite (LSCF)-Samarium-Doped Ceria (SDC) Composite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The effect of SDCC composite electrolyte content on the diffraction pattern, microstructure, specific surface area, and electrochemical performances of the LSCF-SDCC composite cathode were evaluated.
Titulo: Carbonate-Based Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite (LSCF)-Samarium-Doped Ceria (SDC) Composite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The XRD pattern revealed that the SDCC phase diffraction peaks vary according to its increasing addition to the system.
Titulo: Carbonate-Based Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite (LSCF)-Samarium-Doped Ceria (SDC) Composite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The introduction of SDCCs within the composite cathode did not change the LSCF phase structure and its specific surface area.
Titulo: Carbonate-Based Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite (LSCF)-Samarium-Doped Ceria (SDC) Composite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, the electrical performance of the realized cell drastically changed with the increase of the SDCC content in the LSCF microstructure.
Titulo: Carbonate-Based Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite (LSCF)-Samarium-Doped Ceria (SDC) Composite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This drastic change can be ascribed to the poor in-plane electronic conduction at the surface of the LSCF cathode layer due to the presence of the insulating phase of SDC and molten carbonate.
Titulo: Carbonate-Based Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite (LSCF)-Samarium-Doped Ceria (SDC) Composite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Among the cathodes investigated, LSCF-30SDCC showed the best cell performance, exhibiting a power density value of 60.3-75.4 mW/cm(2) at 600 degrees C to 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Carbonate-Based Lanthanum Strontium Cobalt Ferrite (LSCF)-Samarium-Doped Ceria (SDC) Composite Cathode for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
